solutions.content:
Imagine we are covering the floor with carpets from left to right. At any point in this exercise, we will be at some point i and have carpetsRemaining carpets remaining. At this point we are only concerned with covering the floor from i to n - 1. 
In other words i can say that the state at any point is fully defined by (current position, carpets remaining)

When we are standing at index i, we have 2 choices
	* either skip this tile and leave it uncovered
	* use one carpet starting from here.

First off, If we are currently on a black tile, it makes no sense to start a new carpet here, so we just move one step to the right. (whatever white tiles we cover by starting here, we can cover from i + 1 and possibly more)
Now that we are on a white tile, 
	* If we apply option 1 and skip this tile, we would expose 1 white tile and continue the exercise from tile i + 1 with the same number of carpets remaining
	* If we apply option 2 and start a new carpet here, we would use one carpet and continue the exercise from tile i + carpetLen.
	we would obviously want to take the option which would expose the minumum number of white tiles. 

If f( i , carpetsRemaining ) represents the minimum number if white tiles exposed for the floor from i to n - 1 with carpetsRemaining carpets remaining, 
//base cases
* if( i >= n) then ans = 0. ( we have fully covered the floor and are standing to the right of it)
* if( carpetsRemaining == 0 ) then ans = number of zeroes from i to n - 1. (We dont have any more carpets and will expose everything here on out)
```
	if(i >= a.length) {
		return 0;
	}
	if(carpets_left == 0) {
		return suffix[i];      //suffix[i] = number of white tiles from index i to n (can be calculated using a simple for loop)
	}
```
//recursive cases
* if( floor[i] == BLACK ) then ans = f ( i + 1, carpetsRemaining). (Just ignore this tile, continue from next index)
* if( floor[i] == WHITE ) then ans = Max of
									* 1 + f( i + 1, carpetsRemaining)      (expose this tile, hence + 1, and continue with same number of carpets)
									* f( i + carpetLen, carpetsRemaining - 1 )      (start a new carpet here, skip carpetLen tiles, but have 1 less carpet)

```
	 // first check if this state has already been visited, if so return the answer already computed
	if(dp[i][carpets_left] != UNVISITED) {      
		return dp[i][carpets_left];
	}
	if(a[i] == BLACK) {
		//this tile is black, skip it
		dp[i][carpets_left] = f(i + 1, carpets_left, a, dp, suffix, carpetLen);
	}
	else {
		//start carpet here
		int start_carpet_here = f(i + carpetLen, carpets_left - 1, a, dp, suffix, carpetLen);
		//dont start carpet here
		int dont_start_carpet_here = 1 + f(i + 1, carpets_left, a, dp, suffix, carpetLen);
		dp[i][carpets_left] = Math.min(start_carpet_here, dont_start_carpet_here);
	}

	return dp[i][carpets_left];
```

There are (n * numCarpets) states, we momoize the result for each state in a 2D array.
Time Complexity: O(n * numCarpets)
Space Complexity: O(n * numCarpets)

Full Code:
```
class Solution {
    private static final int UNVISITED = -1;
    private static final char BLACK = '0';
    private static final char WHITE = '1';

    private int f(int i, int carpets_left, char[] a, int[][] dp, int[] suffix, int carpetLen) {
        if(i >= a.length) {
            return 0;
        }
        if(carpets_left == 0) {
            return suffix[i];
        }
        if(dp[i][carpets_left] != UNVISITED) {
            return dp[i][carpets_left];
        }
        if(a[i] == BLACK) {
            dp[i][carpets_left] = f(i + 1, carpets_left, a, dp, suffix, carpetLen);
        }
        else {
            //start carpet here
            int start = f(i + carpetLen, carpets_left - 1, a, dp, suffix, carpetLen);
            //dont start carpet here
            int dont = 1 + f(i + 1, carpets_left, a, dp, suffix, carpetLen);

            dp[i][carpets_left] = Math.min(start, dont);
        }

        return dp[i][carpets_left];
    }

    public int minimumWhiteTiles(String floor, int numCarpets, int carpetLen) {

        int n = floor.length();
        char[] a = floor.toCharArray();

        //calculating the suffix array
        int[] suffix = new int[n + 1];
        for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            suffix[i] = suffix[i + 1];
            if(a[i] == WHITE) {
                suffix[i] ++;
            }
        }

        int[][] dp = new int[n + 1][numCarpets + 1];
        for(int[] row : dp) {
            Arrays.fill(row, UNVISITED);
        }

        return f(0, numCarpets, a, dp, suffix, carpetLen);
    }
}
```

