When submitting the normal way, LeetCode reports times around 150 ms and varying quite a bit even when submitting the same solution multiple times. And by now I hope it's well-known that these times usually reflect mostly the judge overhead, barely the actual solution time at all, so they're pretty much useless and just misleading. In this problem, actual solution times seem to be around 4 to 16 ms, and when measured properly, the times are impressively stable. Here are my benchmark results of a few solutions (for each solution I show the best three total times out of ten):
```
findClosestNumberB   3.40 ms   3.42 ms   3.42 ms
findClosestNumberC   3.44 ms   3.44 ms   3.44 ms
findClosestNumberD   3.78 ms   3.78 ms   3.78 ms
