	1. Use 2 variables: "min" to store minimum difference (absolute), and "closest" to store number closest to 0
	2. For each "num" in arrays nums:
		- keep updating values of min and closest. 
		- Note: as mentioned in question; if min == diff, in that case update "closest" with the number which is bigger (num v/s closest).
