solutions.content:
For each circle, we enumerate all lattice points of the square region. If that point is within the radius, we increase the number of points.

We use 2-d array (`g`) to make sure we count "shared" lattice points once.

**C++**
```cpp
int countLatticePoints(vector<vector<int>>& circles) {
    int res = 0, g[201][201] = {};
    for (const auto &c : circles)
        for (int dx = -c[2]; dx <= c[2]; ++dx)
            for (int dy = -c[2]; dy <= c[2]; ++dy)
                if (dx * dx + dy * dy <= c[2] * c[2])
                    res += ++g[c[0] + dx][c[1] + dy] == 1;
    return res;
}  
```

