# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
I guess you already know the question , its quite understandable .
I don't know why i am obsessed with recursion , the first approach came to my mind after seeing most question is if i can somehow use memoization. So here is result of that.
# This solution uses 56.2MB of space 
Don't ask me how just see the solution you will get why.
![image.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/52b50289-814f-4e2c-a5bc-9ca839224059_1680589074.305046.png)

It's okay with run time i guess beats 55%.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. We start from the center and move in all four directions
2. If we already visited the point for current circle , we return 0
3. If we have already encountered the point in any other circle , we don't count it
4. and if point is out of circle , we return 0

Please Suggest any methods to optimise the code.
Thanks
