solutions.content:
**FOR A POINT TO LIE INSIDE A CIRCLE, IT SHOULD FOLLOW A CERTAIN CONDITION**

THE CONDITION IS

**(X-X1)^2 + (Y-Y1)^2 <= (R * R)**

HERE X AND Y IS THE CENTER POINT OF THE CIRCLE,  X1 AND Y1 ARE ANY RANDOM POINTS

NOW, **THE QUESTION COMES HOW TO FIND ALL X1 AND Y1 POINTS** 

NOW LET US ASSUME THAT WE ARE GIVEN A CIRCLE WITH **CENTER (2,2) AND RADIUS 2**

NOW IF WE THINK , WHAT CAN BE THE EXTREME LEFT AND RIGHT POINTS, IT MEANS THAT THE EXTREME LEFT POINT LYING INSIDE THE CIRCLE WILL BE 

THIS CAN BE SIMPLY CALCULATED AS **(CENTER X COORDINATE - RADIUS)**
(2-2) = 0       
THE EXTREME RIGHT POINT WILL BE **( CENTER X COORDINATE + RADIUS)**
(2+2) = 4

IT MEANS THAT X1 COORDINATE WILL LIE IN THE RANGE (0<=X1<=4)

NOW, SIMILARLY WHAT CAN BE THE EXTREME UPWARDS AND DOWNWARDS POINTS

EXTREME DOWNWARD POINT =  **( CENTER Y COORDINATE - RADIUS )**
(2-2) = 0
EXTREME UPWARD POINT  = **(CENTER Y COORDINATE + RADIUS)**
(2+2) = 4
IT MEANS THAT Y1 COORDINATE WILL LIE IN THE RANGE (0<=Y1<=4)

THE ABOVE MENTIONED THINGS CAN BE SIMPLY UNDERSTOOD WITH THE HELP OF DIAGRAM

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/0f3bff1a-6772-458c-93d6-ba83b37a1de7_1650777372.220716.jpeg)

NOW, WE KNOW THAT **X1 WILL RANGE FROM 0 TO 4** AND **Y1 WILL RANGE FROM 0 TO 4**

SO NOW WE HAVE TO TRY EVERY COMBINATION OF THE TWO RANGES AND FOR EVERY COMBINATION WE HAVE TO APPLY THIS FORMULA

**(X-X1)^2 + (Y-Y1)^2 <= (R * R)**

AND IF IT IS TRUE THEN WE HAVE TO JUST INSERT THE COORDINATES IN OUR SET.

WE WILL BE CHOOSING A SET BECAUSE WE DON'T WANT OUR COORDINATES TO BE REPEATED FOR SOME OTHER CIRCLE

**OUR ANS WILL BE THE SIZE OF THE SET**
THE CODE IS AS FOLLOWS 
```
class Solution {
public:

    void solve(int x,int y,int r, set<pair<int,int>>&jd )
    {

        int a = x-r;
        int b = x+r;

        int c = y-r;
        int d = y+r;

        for(int i=a; i<=b; i++)
        {
            for(int j=c; j<=d; j++)
            {
                int z = (x-i)*(x-i);
                int t = (y-j)*(y-j);
                int m = r*r;
                if(z+t<=m)
                {
               //     cout<<x-i<<" "<<y-j<<" "<<endl;
                    jd.insert(make_pair(i,j));
                }
            }
        }



    }


    int countLatticePoints(vector<vector<int>>& circles) {

        set<pair<int,int>>jd;

        for(int i=0; i<circles.size(); i++)
        {

            int x = circles[i][0];
            int y = circles[i][1];
            int r = circles[i][2];
            solve(x,y,r,jd);


        }
        int ans = jd.size();
        return ans;






    }
};
```

