# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
if the distance between a point and the centre is less than or equal to the radius then the point is in the circle.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
each circle would be boxed in a square of length 2*r.
Number of points in the square = (2*r+1)^2.
Calculate the distance between each point and the centre if its less than the length of the radius then the point is inside the circle.
We push the points in a set to as to eliminate repetitions. 
In the end we return the size of the set.


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int countLatticePoints(vector<vector<int>>& nums) {
        int dis=0;
        set<pair<int,int>> v;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++)
        {
            int x=nums[i][0]-nums[i][2],y=nums[i][1]-nums[i][2];
            int x1=nums[i][0]+nums[i][2],y1=nums[i][1]+nums[i][2];
            for(int k=x;k<=x1;k++)
            {
                for(int j=y;j<=y1;j++)
                {
                    if( (j-nums[i][1])*(j-nums[i][1]) + (k-nums[i][0])*(k-nums[i][0]) <= nums[i][2] * nums[i][2] ) 
                    {
                        pair<int,int> m=make_pair(k,j);
                        v.insert(m);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        return v.size();
    }
};
```

