solutions.content:
For any point `(p, q)` in a square of `(x\xB1r, y\xB1r) `, we would want to check if it is a lattice point. 
Let `long_pole` and `short_pole` to represent the max and min value of `abs(p - x)` and `abs(q - y)`.
When `long_pole >= r/2`, we would want to know the max value of  `short_pole` so that for any `shot_pole` equal or below that value, `(p, q)` is lattice point.

Since `r <= 200`, this information can be precalculated.

We track the found lattice points with a hash set.

The precalculated results are too large and it cannot fit into this thread. Using `<PRECALCULATED_RESULTS>` to represent it.

Precalculation
