**Intutuion** : If you want to get maximum number by deleting we have to replace it by bigger number else we have to delete the last occurence of the digit. 
So here we store the index of the occurence of digit and check if the next number is bigger than the number then we break out of loop and remove that number else we remove the last occurence of the digit

```
class Solution {
public:
    string removeDigit(string number, char digit) {
        int idx=-1;
       int n=number.size();
        for(int i=0;i<number.size();i++){
            if(number[i]==digit){
                idx=i;
            }
            if(idx!=-1 && idx!=n-1){
                if(number[idx+1]>digit)
                    break;
            }
        }
        number.erase(number.begin()+idx);
        return number;

    }
};
