solutions.content:
**Time Complexity**:   `O(N)`

**Approach:**
Take the following examples:
* 9292929 with digit as 9 :
	we will try to delete 9 from the rightmost side
* 1212121 with digit as 1:
	try to delete from leftmost side
* 8282898 with digit as 8
	for this one, position is 4 (0-indexed) 

From the above observations we can deduce that we will check if the current digit is greater than the digit to the immediate right then we will store the position as the last occurence for the position to be deleted. Else, the digit is removed and returned.

After the loop is traversed and nothing is returned, then we shall delete the position in last occurence(`lastocc`) and returned.

**Special Case:** we are not checking for the last character is equal to digit or not.... so there is a possibility of wrong answer. Hence, i'm checking the position and updating the value of last occurence (`lastocc`)

**Code:**

```
class Solution {
    public String removeDigit(String number, char digit) {
        int len=number.length(),lastocc=len-1;//lastocc can be initialized with any value
        for(int i=0;i<len-1;i++){
            char ch=number.charAt(i),chnext=number.charAt(i+1);
            if(ch==digit)
                if(ch>=chnext)
                    lastocc=i;
                else return number.substring(0,i)+number.substring(i+1);
        }
        lastocc=number.charAt(len-1)==digit? len-1 : lastocc;//updating lastocc for SPECIAL CASE
        return number.substring(0,lastocc)+number.substring(lastocc+1);
    }
}
```

