solutions.content:
# Approach
Scan from left to right. If the next digit is bigger than the target (aka `digit` described in problem) one,  it will be the optimal solution.
If every next digits always as same as, or less than the target, then delete the rightmost target. Because you always need to maximize the result, so if you fall into this case, delete the rightmost one is the prefered solution.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$
- Space complexity:
$$O(1)$$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string removeDigit(string number, char digit) {
        int n=0;

        while((n=number.find(digit, n)) != string::npos){
            if(n!=number.length()-1 && number[n+1]>number[n]){
                number.erase(n,1);
                return number;
            }
            n++;
        }

        number.erase(number.rfind(digit), 1);
        return number;
    }
};
```

