solutions.content:
Detect the digit. We want to maximize the number. So if the next number is greater than the digit, we get rid of it and make it bigger.
If not, then by removing the current digit, we make the number smaller. It's best to delete the furthest position, as down-sizing of the number will be minimized. Thus we only keep the latest index of the digit.
```
var removeDigit = function(number, digit) {
    let idx;

    for (let i = 0; i < number.length; i++) {
        if (number[i] == digit) {

			// By deleting this digit, the number gets larger.
            if (number[i+1] > digit) {
                return number.slice(0, i) + number.slice(i+1);
            }

			// By deleting this digit, the number gets smaller. We keep the index and continue to see if there is 
			// another digit that will make the number larger later on. If that's not the case in the end, 
			// we delete the furthest of such to minimize the loss.
            else {
                idx = i;
            }
        }
    }

    return number.slice(0, idx) + number.slice(idx+1);
};
```

