solutions.content:
**Key Point**:  Position the carpet at the beginning of each set of tiles(Greedy). 

**Justification of Greedy Approach**: This is since, in case we don't do this (let's say the candidate starting position is a few places right of the starting position of a set of tiles, we may have lost a few tiles on the right, since it may be empty space instead of tiles - where the carpet has moved to)

We then use Binary Search to figure out which set of tiles, the carpet extends to 
```
class Solution {
    int[][] tiles;
    int[] tileSum;
    public int maximumWhiteTiles(int[][] tiles, int carpetLen) {
        this.tiles = tiles;
        this.tileSum = new int[tiles.length];

        Arrays.sort(tiles, (a, b) -> (a[0] - b[0]));
        for(int i = 0; i < tiles.length; i++) tileSum[i] = ((i > 0) ? tileSum[i - 1] : 0) + (tiles[i][1] - tiles[i][0] + 1);

        int maxLength = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < tiles.length; i++) {
            //carpeting starts at leftMost idx of tiles[i]
            int endCoordinate = tiles[i][0] + carpetLen - 1;
            int tileIdx = idxOfFurthestTileWithLeftMostIdxLessThanOrEqualTo(i, endCoordinate);
            int usedCarpetLength;

            if(tileIdx == 0) usedCarpetLength = 0;
            else usedCarpetLength = tileSum[tileIdx - 1] - (i == 0 ?  0 : tileSum[i - 1]);

            if(endCoordinate > tiles[tileIdx][1]) usedCarpetLength += (tiles[tileIdx][1] - tiles[tileIdx][0] + 1);
            else usedCarpetLength += (endCoordinate - tiles[tileIdx][0] + 1);

            maxLength = Math.max(usedCarpetLength, maxLength);
        }

        return maxLength;
    }

    public int idxOfFurthestTileWithLeftMostIdxLessThanOrEqualTo(int l, int val) {
        int r = tiles.length - 1;
        int rightMost = -1;
        while(l <= r) {
            int mid = (l + r)/2;
            if(tiles[mid][0] < val) {
                rightMost = Math.max(rightMost, mid);
                l = mid + 1;
            } else if (tiles[mid][0] > val) {
                r = mid - 1;
            } else {
                rightMost = Math.max(rightMost, mid);
                break;
            }
        }
        return rightMost;
    }
}
```

