Approach-1: Brute Force
Going with the brute force will take O(N^3) as N^2 for finding all the subarray and N for doing the operation for min value and sum.
Approach-2: Optimised to O(N^2 log)
we can store the min value(segment tree) and prefix sum and use it for each subarray but it will still take O(N^2).
Approach-3: Optimised to N
Intuition behind this is to fix the min element and find all the subarray sum which incudes this element.

Algorithm used:
1. calculate the presum of presum in an array(presum[k] is the sum of first k elemnt array)
2. find the immediate smaller number index on left side
3. find immediate smaller or equal munber index on right side
4. use pre array to find the sum of all subarry which contains ith element as min element ans multiply it with a[i].

return the sum of strenght stored in ans

