# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Monotonic Stack to maintain a raising min stack.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
Ref: @lee215 https://leetcode.com/problems/sum-of-total-strength-of-wizards/solutions/2061985/java-c-python-one-pass-solution/?orderBy=most_votes
```
class Solution {
    public int totalStrength(int[] ss) {
        int presum = 0, res = 0, n = ss.length, mod = (int) 1e9 + 7;
        Stack<Integer> st = new Stack<>(); // monotonic mins from left;
        int[] acc = new int[n + 2];
        for (int r = 0; r <= n; r++) {
            // append 0 to end of ary. to better sum cases of group ending at tail.
            int curr = r < n ? ss[r] : 0; 
            presum = (presum + curr) % mod;
            //acc[r+1] sums all pregroup ends before or at ss[r];
            acc[r + 1] = (acc[r] + presum) % mod; 
            while(!st.isEmpty() && ss[st.peek()] > curr) {
                //because we met new min, so we have to sum all groups with prev mins
                int i = st.pop(); // new min to calculate;
                // l is -1 means group starts from head of ary
                int l = st.isEmpty() ? -1 : st.peek();
                // all sum of pregroups ending with (l, i), exclusive;
                int leftAcc = l < 0 ? acc[i] : acc[i] - acc[l];
                // all sum of pregroups ending with (i, r), exclusive;
                long rightAcc = acc[r] - acc[i];
                long leftCount = i - l, rightCount = r - i;
                // all sums of combinations from left subgroup + right subgroup.
                // proval is trival. 
                res = (int) (res + (rightAcc * leftCount - leftAcc * rightCount) % mod * ss[i] % mod) % mod;
            }
            // now st is empty or curr >= st.peek();
            // so push to maintain monotonic stack;
            st.push(r);
        }
        return (res + mod) % mod;
    }
}
```

