# Intuition
This is a problem that I have to spend so much time to find out the answer.And finally here is my answer

# Approach
The problem can be broken down into 2 main parts:
- Finding left and right boundaries that each strength[i] is min
- Finding how to calculate the sum of all subarrays that strength[i] is min
The hard part is the second one, the first one can be solved just by using stacks. 
For the second part, here is an example of how to calculate the sum of all subarrays:
```
Consider array: 3 2 3 4
All the array that 2 will be min is:
3 2
3 2 3
3 2 3 4
2 3
2 3 4
```
So you can see we have 3, 2 in the left of 2 and we have 3 and 4 in the right of 2. Each elements at j in the left of 2 (2 is at i) will happens (j - left + 1)*(right - i + 1) and each elements in the right will happens (i - left + 1)*(right - j + 1).
Break it down in details will be:
From left to i:

```
SUM[(j - left + 1)*(right-i + 1)*strength[j]];
= (right - i + 1)*SUM[(j - left + 1)*strength[j]];
= (right - i + 1)*[SUM[j*strength[j]] - (left - 1)*SUM[strength[j]]];
```
From i+1 to right:
```
SUM[(i - left + 1)*(right - j + 1)*strength[j]];
= (i - left + 1)*SUM[(right - j + 1)*strength[j]];
= (i - left + 1)*[(right+1)*SUM[strength[j]] - SUM[j*strength[j]]];
```

If we break it down, we will find out that we need prefixSum (strength[j]) and prefixProd (strength[j]*j) to find out the sum of all subarrays in O(1)
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int n;
    public long MOD = 1000000007;
    public int totalStrength(int[] strength) {
        n = strength.length;

        long[] leftBoundaries = new long[n];
        long[] rightBoundaries = new long[n];
        long[] prefixProd = new long[n];
        long[] prefixSum = new long[n];

        helperProd(prefixProd, strength);
        helperSum(prefixSum, strength);

        Arrays.fill(rightBoundaries, n - 1);
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && strength[stack.peek()] > strength[i]){
                rightBoundaries[stack.pop()] = i - 1;
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }
        stack.clear();
        for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && strength[stack.peek()] >= strength[i]){
                leftBoundaries[stack.pop()] = i + 1;
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }
        long result = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            long left = leftBoundaries[i];
            long right = rightBoundaries[i];
            long sum = 0;
            sum += addLeft(left, right, i, prefixProd, prefixSum);
            sum += addRight(left, right, i, prefixProd, prefixSum);
            result += ((sum*(long)strength[i])%MOD);
            result %= MOD;
        }
        return (int) (result%MOD);
    }
    void helperProd(long[] a, int[] b){
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            a[i] = ((long)b[i]*(long)i + (i >= (long)1 ? a[i - 1] : (long)0));
        }
    }
    void helperSum(long[] a, int[] b){
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            a[i] = (long)b[i] + (i >= 1 ? a[i - 1] : (long)0);
        }
    }
    long addLeft(long left, long right, int i, long[] prod, long[] sum){
        long a = (right - (long) i + 1)%MOD;
        long b = (prod[i] - (left >= 1 ? prod[(int)left - 1] : (long) 0) - (left - (long)1)*(sum[i] - (left >= 1 ? sum[(int)left - 1] : (long) 0)))%MOD;
        long result = a*b;
        return result % MOD;
    }
    long addRight(long left, long right, int i, long[] prod, long[] sum){
        long a = ((long)i - left + 1)%MOD;
        long b = ((right + 1)*(sum[(int)right] - sum[i]) - prod[(int)right] + prod[i])%MOD;
        long result = a*b;
        return result % MOD;
    }
}
```

