The initial commented code is what I could come up in the contest.
I could find the problem: https://leetcode.com/submissions/detail/704911289/ but couldnt find sum of left and right subarrays in O(n) during contest. However, the video linked is quite useful to understand the last part.

For [1,3,1,2] example,
my prefix is [0,1,4,5,7]
and preprefix is [0,1,5,10,17]

Now, the monotonic stack will ensure that it will give all indexes [variable j] and their corresponding leftptr[variable k] and rightptr [variable i].

Hence the count of elements in leftside of j is left = j-k;
and count of elements in rightside of j is right = i-j

With that, we can find the terms to be minus and plus from the prefix_of_prefix sum
[Refer : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HYCMvFxWO7w&t=1660s]
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/f253cd5f-7704-45ba-b439-ba9103c3c7ac_1653242603.9380913.png)

PS : Be careful with MODs -> I try to do at every LONG manipulation step and if there is  subtraction, I just add MOD to avoid numbers being negative. 

Hope below helps!

```
class Solution {
    public int totalStrength(int[] arr) {

        long MOD = 1000000007;
        int n = arr.length;
        long[] prefix = new long[n+1];
        long[] preprefix = new long[n+1];

        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++) {
            prefix[i] = prefix[i-1]+arr[i-1];
            preprefix[i] = preprefix[i-1]+prefix[i]; //creating prefix of prefix
        }

        long ans=0;

        //BELOW IS O(N^2) - GIVES TLE
//         for(int b=1;b<=n;b++) {
//             long min=Long.MAX_VALUE;
//             for( int l=0;l<n && b+l<=n;l++) {
//                 min = Math.min(min, strength[b+l-1]);
//                 long sum = prefix[b+l]-prefix[b-1];

//                 ans = (ans + (min*sum)%MOD)%MOD;
//                 // System.out.println("Begin:"+(b-1)+ "End:" + (b+l-1)+":"+ min+":" + sum);
//             }
//         }

        //THIS IS O(N) -> Monotonic stack + prefix sum + prefix_of_prefix sum
        // Took hints from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HYCMvFxWO7w&t=1660s and https://leetcode.com/submissions/detail/704911289/
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();
        int j, k;

        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {
            // System.out.println("i is "+i);
            //  System.out.println("Stack is "+stack.toString());
            while (!stack.isEmpty() && arr[stack.peek()] > (i == n ? Integer.MIN_VALUE : arr[i])) {
                j = stack.pop();
                k = stack.isEmpty() ? -1 : stack.peek();
                int left = j-k;
                int right = i-j;

                // if j is the min index
                // preprefix[j] -> preprefix till before it till prevptr's prefix [not including itself]

                long minus = preprefix[j] -  (k==-1? 0: preprefix[k]); // how many ends before i
                minus = (minus%MOD+MOD)%MOD;

                // preprefix[i] -> preprefix till nextptr's prefix till before j's prefix [since we want to count from j each time]
                long plus = preprefix[i] - preprefix[j]; // how many ends after i
                plus = (plus%MOD+MOD)%MOD;

                // min_value -> left_count : right_count -> prevptr : curr : nextptr -> minus: plus
                // System.out.println(arr[j] +":" +(j-k) +":" + (i-j) + " OK " + k +":" +j+":"+i + " OK " + minus +":" + plus);


                // SUM OF ALL SUBARRAYS   *   MINIMUM 
                // Adding MOD as we dont want it to be negative in sum of subarrays

                ans += (((plus*left)%MOD - (minus*right)%MOD + MOD )%MOD) * arr[j] ;
                ans %=MOD;
            }
            stack.push(i);
        }

        return (int)(ans%MOD);
    }
}

